      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Finals Day at Flemington and we kick off with the 2yo sprinters where STARS OF DOM (4) looks ideally suited getting to 1200m at her third start. Two runs to date have been very good over 1000m. She charged home on debut and then chased one with a big spruik last time. She gets in nicely and looks the one to beat. ONE DAY AT A TIME (3) resumes. She tackled some good races in her maiden campaign including a trip to Queensland. The debut here when crossing the line with Streisand reads well. VIVID STORM (1) is the only horse to have won a race in the field, finishing too well at Caulfield Heath over this trip. He's up and running and will take some getting by. Wary of RESOLUTELY (7) who resumes off a decent break. She chased home Guest House on debut in solid time which has worked out very well. She gets in light and can figure prominently fresh. STELLAR CIPHER (5) next best.",
